The paper discusses issues related to implementing algorithms and benchmarking in scientific software development, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new open platform for scientific software development. cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also relevant as the paper discusses the challenges of implementing algorithms in new codebases. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are relevant as the paper discusses issues related to computational disciplines such as systems biology. cs.DB (Databases) is also relevant as the paper discusses the development of fair and widely available benchmark sets.
